  "body": "This is a valid config:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.7.3\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    rinkeby: {\r\n      url: \"https://rinkeby.infura.io/v3/\",\r\n      accounts: [\"0xaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa\"]\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut adding or removing a single character to the private key (or changing an `a` to a `g`) results in this error message:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError HH8: There's one or more errors in your config file:\r\n\r\n  * Invalid value {\"url\":\"https://rinkeby.infura.io/v3/\",\"accounts\":[\"0xaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa\"]} for HardhatConfig.networks.rinkeby - Expected a value of type HttpNetworkConfig.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere is a bigger issue here about our config validation being awful in general, but I think we should handle this particular case right now, since it shows up **a lot** in the discord server, and it's a really bad experience for users.",
